{id:"api-2014-spells-wall-of-fire",name:"Wall of Fire",content:[{id:"Title",content:"Wall of Fire"},{id:"StatGrid",content:[{title:"Level",content:"4"},{title:"Casting Time",content:"1 action"},{title:"Range",content:"120 feet (60ft line)"},{title:"Components",content:"V, S, M"},{title:"Duration",content:"Up to 1 minute"},{title:"School",content:"Evocation"},{title:"Save",content:"DEX Save"},{title:"Damage",content:"Fire"}]},{id:"Subtitle",content:"Effect"},{id:"MultiText",content:["You create a wall of fire on a solid surface within range. You can make the wall up to 60 feet long, 20 feet high, and 1 foot thick, or a ringed wall up to 20 feet in diameter, 20 feet high, and 1 foot thick. The wall is opaque and lasts for the duration.","When the wall appears, each creature within its area must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 5d8 fire damage, or half as much damage on a successful save.","One side of the wall, selected by you when you cast this spell, deals 5d8 fire damage to each creature that ends its turn within 10 feet o f that side or inside the wall. A creature takes the same damage when it enters the wall for the first time on a turn or ends its turn there. The other side of the wall deals no damage.","The other side of the wall deals no damage."]},{id:"Subtitle",content:"At higher levels"},{id:"MultiText",content:["When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 4th."]},{id:"Table",content:[["slot level","4"],["damage","5d8"]]}]}